The President of the United States, in a statement, expressed his satisfaction with the Senate's confirmation of John Kerry as the next Secretary of State. He praised Kerry's service in Vietnam and his years in the Senate, highlighting his dedication to American global leadership. The President believes that Kerry's experience and respect from world leaders, as well as bipartisan support in the Senate, make him well-suited for the role. The President looks forward to working with Kerry to maintain American leadership and promote the nation's interests and values.